<br>
1.  Not every batter can place hit.  If a pitcher consistantly pitches outside on lefty who can only hit down the 1st base line, then you know I don't feel sorry for em if it happens.  You have pitchers out there that try to be fancy with the way the spin the ball or place a ball and don't realize that some of these guys will come up the middle if you are not paying attention.  Not because they plan to, but because they just can't control the placement of their hit as well as others.<br>
<br>
2.  There are those place hitters that do like to try and decapitate the pitcher intentionally cause they either think its funny, or dislike the guy or the team they are on, or plain and simple...cause they can.  Guys like that make this game dangerous for pitchers and to be honest, the main reason most do it is because..they don't have to pitch.<br>
