<br>
E- it is considered part of the game but generally considered an open invite for the other team<br>
<br>
D- it is still considered ok but players whom have played upper levels probably refrain against it.<br>
<br>
C- considered a direct attempt to hit the pitcher. Will be retaliation by the other team most likely(usually this is where the pitcher hands the ball over to the offending player if he is smart{this class has enough pop to kill someone})<br>
<br>
B- if you do it you are probably not regarded in the best way.<br>
<br>
A and above- almost always an accident, can and will kill someone. Refrained by all players as much probably by fear of retaliation as for respect for the other team.<br>
<br>
Oh and my two cents (and I pitch) I hit to the sides of the pitcher on occassion and if you do it just be ready to pitch. And I probably have been hit at by as many as anyone in the game. And just for the record I have been hit twice in my life both times it hurt like hell!!!!!!!!!!!!<br>
